VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(?:query|execute|prepare)\s*!?\s*\(\s*["'][^"']*(?:\{\}|\+)
WHEN EXPR MISSING:query!\s*\(|sqlx::query!|prepare\s*\(|bind\s*\(|QueryBuilder|params|bindParams && MISSING:test|example
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects likely dynamic SQL string construction in database calls.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Potential SQL Query Concatenation.
